# Better-Auth Rules

Better-Auth is the authentication layer. Self-hosted, data stored in our own Postgres.

## Configuration

- Auth config lives in `lib/auth.ts`
- Use the ZenStack adapter (`@zenstackhq/better-auth`)
- Organizations plugin is enabled — all consultant accounts belong to an org

## Authentication Flows

- **Consultants:** Standard email/password or OAuth via Better-Auth. Users belong to an organization.
- **Suppliers:** Magic Links scoped to a single project/supplier pair. No account creation required. No dashboard access.

## Security

- Never store auth secrets in code — environment variables only (`BETTER_AUTH_SECRET`)
- Session tokens must be validated server-side before any data access
- Magic Link tokens should have short TTLs and be single-use
